---
source: crates/oxc_linter/src/tester.rs
---

  ⚠ unicorn(no-array-for-each): Do not use `Array#forEach`
   ╭─[no_array_for_each.tsx:1:5]
 1 │ foo.forEach?.(element => bar(element))
   ·     ───────
   ╰────
  help: Replace it with a `for…of` loop. It is faster, more readable, and allows early exits with `break` or `return`.

  ⚠ unicorn(no-array-for-each): Do not use `Array#forEach`
   ╭─[no_array_for_each.tsx:1:4]
 1 │ 1?.forEach((a, b) => call(a, b))
   ·    ───────
   ╰────
  help: For arrays that need the index, replace it with a `for…of` loop over `.entries()`, such as `for (const [index, element] of array.entries())`. Otherwise, use the appropriate `for…of` loop. Array `.entries()` keeps indexes numeric and loops allow early exits with `break` or `return`.

  ⚠ unicorn(no-array-for-each): Do not use `Array#forEach`
   ╭─[no_array_for_each.tsx:1:7]
 1 │ array.forEach((arrayInArray) => arrayInArray.forEach(element => bar(element)));
   ·       ───────
   ╰────
  help: Replace it with a `for…of` loop. It is faster, more readable, and allows early exits with `break` or `return`.

