  ⚠ unicorn(no-array-for-each): Do not use `Array#forEach`
   ╭─[no_array_for_each.tsx:1:5]
 1 │ foo.forEach((value, ...rest) => { bar(rest); });
   ·     ───────
   ╰────
  help: Replace it with a `for…of` loop that preserves the extra callback arguments you use. For arrays, `.entries()` provides the numeric index, and the original array can be referenced directly if needed.

